DOCUMENT();
############################################################ # Load Macros ############################################################ loadMacros( "PGstandard.pl", "PGML.pl", "AnswerFormatHelp.pl", "PCCmacros.pl", "parserLinearRelation.pl", "PGcourse.pl", ); COMMENT('Authored in PreTeXt');
############################################################ # Header ############################################################ TEXT(beginproblem());
############################################################ # PG Setup Code ############################################################ Context("LinearRelation")->variables->are(x => 'Real'); $equation = LinearRelation("x + 0.19x = 150");
############################################################ # Body ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML Kirima offered to pay the bill and tip at a restaurant where she and her friends had dinner. In total she paid [`\$150`] even, where the tip was a little more than [`19\%\text{.}`] We'd like to know what was the bill before tip. Set up an equation for this situation.
[@KeyboardInstructions('Use [|x|]* for any variable you define and use.')@]**
[_]{$equation}{25}
END_PGML
############################################################ # Solution ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION A common mistake is to translate a question like this into "what is [`19\%`] of [`\$150\text{?}`]" as a way to calculate the tip amount, and then subtract that from [`\$150\text{.}`] But that is not how tipping works. The [`19\%`] is applied to the _original bill_, not the _final total_. So please read carefully.
If we let [`x`] represent the original bill, we can apply (1.1.2) and we have:
[```\newcommand{\pinover}[2]{\overset{\overset{\mathrm{\ #2\ }}{|}}{\strut #1 \strut}}\newcommand{\amp}{&} \begin{aligned} \pinover{x}{bill}\pinover{+}{plus}\pinover{0.19}{19\%}\pinover{\cdot}{of}\pinover{x}{bill}\amp\pinover{=}{is}\pinover{150}{\$150} \end{aligned} ```]
Again, we are not currently trying to solve this equation, just write it down.
END_PGML_SOLUTION
############################################################ # End Problem ############################################################
ENDDOCUMENT();
